  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer. The registration itself is trivial (one line); the value of this task is the
    formal review against ADR-010 (DI Minimalism) + the asymmetric-registration anti-pattern rule (bff-extensions
    §F.1). Confirm both endpoint-mapping and service registration are UNCONDITIONAL.
  </role>

  <goal>
    AiCompletionNodeExecutor DI registration complete + verified:
    1. AnalysisServicesModule.AddNodeExecutors registers AiCompletionNodeExecutor as Singleton
    2. Registration is UNCONDITIONAL (no feature-flag wrap — there is no per-customer toggle for this)
    3. Placed alphabetically near sibling executors (between AiAnalysis and AgentService or per existing ordering)
    4. DI graph resolves cleanly: app builds + starts without exception
    5. NodeExecutorRegistry.Resolve(ExecutorType.AiCompletion) returns the new executor instance
    6. No asymmetric-registration anti-pattern (per bff-extensions §F.1): executor registration + any consuming endpoint mapping are both unconditional
    7. Smoke test at startup confirms executor count (existing N executors + 1 new = N+1)
  </goal>

  <inputs>
