  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — Singleton registration via AddNodeExecutors helper; no extra abstraction layers; no factory.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — IInvokePlaybookAi triangle stays canonical; this registration is a leaf-executor addition.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF Publish Hygiene — task 010 runs the full publish + CVE. This task contributes ~0 bytes (single registration line).</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F.1">Asymmetric-Registration Tier 1.5 Anti-Pattern — verify executor registration is unconditional. The orchestrator dispatches by ExecutorType from sprk_executortype column unconditionally; no feature flag wraps this executor. P1 Promote-to-unconditional pattern applies by default.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene — placement unchanged (IN BFF, leaf executor). PR description does not need a new placement justification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F">Test update obligation — DI registrations are explicitly EXCLUDED from unit-test obligations per ADR-038 (DI-registration tests are a banned anti-pattern). This task does NOT add a "registration exists" test.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — do NOT add a "service is registered" unit test. Smoke-test via runtime resolution (e.g., the registry hands back a non-null instance), but no Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection introspection test.</constraint>
  </constraints>

